productBaseInfoV1.title: Tefal TEF-FV3680 Steam Iron
productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: The Tefal Superglide FV3680 steam iron boasts 2200 watts, a 95g/min shot of steam, along with 0-35g/min variable steam. The FV3680 offers vertical steam, for easily de-creasing hanging garments such as suit and dresses, and even curtains. The steam output of an iron is indicated in grams per minute (g/min), so the higher the output, the more steam is generated to tackle creases. And the more powerful the iron, the deeper steam will penetrate fabric for quicker, hassle-free ironing and excellent results, no matter the fabric. The FV3680 features Tefal's Ultraglide ceramic soleplate for superior glideability, scratch resistance and steam distribution. Tefal has also responded to customer feedback and designed a refilling station at the front of the iron which offers not only added safety, but an ultra-fast four-second refill. The iron has an extra wide heel for convenient cord storage, and added stability and safety. It is also anti scale, a three metre cord and a convenient 270ml water tank.

productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: The Tefal Maestro FV3764 steam iron combines power and efficiency with low maintenance. It offers a powerful 2200 wattage and 0-30g/minute steam output, to gently soften clothes for easier ironing. The Tefal Maestro also boasts an 85g/minute shot of steam, a boost to get rid of those more difficult and stubborn creases. The steam output of an iron is indicated in grams per minute (g/min), so the higher the output, the more steam is generated to tackle creases. And the more powerful the iron, the deeper steam will penetrate fabric for quicker, hassle-free ironing and excellent results, no matter the fabric. The Tefal Maestro FV3764 features a durable stainless steel soleplate for smooth ironing with minimum surface resistance. The FV3764 also features a soft handle with an elegant design, as well as a large 300ml water tank and a 2.5m cord length. Thanks to its vertical steam ability, you will also be able to give a fresh touch to your hanging garments, suits and curtains. The FV3764 has a double anti-scale system for easy maintenance and long lasting performance and also features an anti-drip function to keep water from leaking onto the clothes you are ironing. productBaseInfoV1.title: Usha SI2730 Steam Iron(White)
productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: The Usha 2730 is a steam iron with a classy look designed for the best ironing results. The Usha 2730 has a Non-stick coated soleplate for perfect ironing. In the times of overheating, this soleplate ensures the safety of your clothes by preventing them from sticking to the iron. The handle of this Usha iron has a comfortable grip for easy manoeuvring. The centrally placed swivel cord on the Usha 2730 steam iron allows free movement of the iron in all directions. This swivel cord protects both your palm and wrist by reducing pressure on them during extended ironing sessions. Steam Features The water tank capacity of the Usha 2730 steam iron is 300 ml. The spray function on this Usha iron releases fine mist to moisten the fabric evenly. This Usha appliance has a variable steam control for ironing clothes made from different kind of fabrics and textures. The continuous steam output of the Usha 2730 is 25 g/m. The steam boost on this Usha iron produces an extra burst of steam for ironing thick fabrics. The Usha 2730 steam iron features a self-clean system which is suitable for tap water. This system removes the scale build-up by flushing the iron. It is recommended to use this function at least once a month for a prolonged life of the iron.Safety and Power This Usha steam iron consumes a maximum power of 1300 W. The Usha 2730 steam iron has automatic overheat shut off feature for operational safety. This feature cuts off electricity supply to the heating element when required. The indicator light on the Usha 2730 steam iron shows when the iron has reached the essential temperature and is ready to use. The voltage required by this Usha device is 230 V for smooth functioning. Note: To avoid leakage of water through the steam vents, please fill the water tank, switch off the steam and plug in. Once the iron is heated for 20-30 seconds, the steam can be switched on.

Since the device does not require cumbersome wiring it is free to be placed anywhere that you see fit. The lack of wires also means that the device charges by Induction method. The device is self contained, which makes it washable under the tap as well.
